            <title>[GROOVY-7997] calling method having a Bigdecimal parameter with a long produces incorrect bigdecimal</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-7997</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Assume the following example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;def x = Random.newInstance().nextLong()

def asBigDecimal(BigDecimal bd){
    println &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;bigdecimal value is $bd&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
}

println &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; value is $x&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
asBigDecimal(x)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will produce two different print outs.&lt;br/&gt;
My expecation is that the printed numbers are equal.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
